{
  "Question": "<p>How do I solve the Diophantine equation <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_303\"><math alttext=\"ax^{2}+bx+c=y^{2}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></semantics></math></span>?</p> <p>The approach I have so far is to use the transformation <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_304\"><math alttext=\"X=2ax+b\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_305\"><math alttext=\"Y=2y\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span>. Applying this, we get, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_306\"><math alttext=\"X^{2}-dY^{2}=n\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>Y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span>, where <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_307\"><math alttext=\"n=b^{2}-4ac\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_308\"><math alttext=\"d=a\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span>.</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_309\"><math alttext=\"X^{2}-dY^{2}=n\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>Y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span> is a Pell equation.</p> <p>Questions:</p> <ol> <li>Is there any other method?</li> <li>What is the complexity of the algorithm for finding the solution to the Pell equation?</li> </ol>",
  "Title": "Method for solving Diophantine equation <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_302\"><math alttext=\"ax^{2}+bx+c=y^{2}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></semantics></math></span>",
  "Tags": "diophantine-equations,computational-complexity,pell-type-equations"
}